{
  "texts": [
    "It also adds several capabilities beyond the browser-based renderer.",
    "It can render multiple channels of an LM image simultaneously, better representing the data used by the PPPM matching algorithm.",
    "It can render multiple EM skeletons simultaneously, which can be useful for verifying fragmented neurons or for comparing several match results at once.",
    "It can also generate animated videos, showing changes to the camera position and other viewing parameters.",
    "Software architectureWe used fully-managed, serverless AWS services to build the back-end (Fig. 12) of the web application, including Cognito identity federation for authentication, IAM for authorization, Lambda for compute, S3 for storage, and DynamoDB as the database."
  ]
